Error code 40038 indicates a "Data declaration error" in the ABB IRC5 system.

Specifically, it means "LOCAL illegal in routine variable declaration." This error occurs when the "LOCAL" attribute is used incorrectly within a routine's variable declaration.

To resolve this, you should either remove the "LOCAL" attribute from the variable declaration or move the declaration outside of the routine. The "LOCAL" attribute is only permitted for program data declarations, not for routine variable declarations.

