### Error Code 10039: Serial Measurement Board Data Incorrect

This error indicates that the data in the Serial Measurement Board (SMB) memory is incorrect. This can happen during startup if the SMB or the main controller has been replaced.

**Solution:**

The recommended solution is to update the Serial Measurement Board data. You can find detailed instructions on how to perform this update in the IRC5 Operator's Manual.

If you would like me to create a work order to have a technician address this issue, please let me know.

